<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>1980:</strong>&nbsp;EyeTap, the first portable computer won in front of the eye, developed by Steve Mann. EyeTap recorded images and superimposed others on it. It could be played by head movements.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong><em>Steve Mann</em></strong><br><a href="https://www.softwaretestinghelp.com/wp-content/qa/uploads/2020/06/Steve-Mann-wearing-a-Generation-4-Glass.jpg"></a></p>
